'I just love Ronda Rousey and I knew she was going to have a very special moment,' added leading man Diesel. 

Rousey currently boasts an 11-0 record in the sport having defeated Cat Zingano in just 14 seconds in her most recent contest on February 28.

However, she recently quashed talk of the prospect of her ever fighting a male opponent in UFC.

'There should never (be) a venue where we're celebrating a man hitting a woman,' she said.

